The paper discusses the use of semantic web technologies and information retrieval techniques to manage and integrate large amounts of geospatial data from open knowledge bases, with a focus on the quality of the data. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), deep learning (cs.DL), and cybersecurity (cs.CY). However, given the emphasis on information retrieval and data quality, cs.IR and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories.
